metadata.title: Beechcraft Super King Air
aws::graph::propositions: Beechcraft Super King Air Models
Model 200C is a civil equivalent to A200C.
36 Model 200C aircraft were built.
Model A200CT is the third military model.
Model A200CT was built for U.S. Army.
Model A200CT has a cargo door.
Model A200CT has wingtip fuel tanks of Model 200T.
93 Model A200CT aircraft were built.
Model 200CT is a civil equivalent to A200CT.
One Model 200CT aircraft was converted from Model 200C.
Model B200 is the current baseline production model.
Model B200 is an updated version of Model 200.
1,157 Model B200 aircraft were built as of the end of 2009.
The 1,157 Model B200 aircraft include those converted to Model B200Ts.
12 Model B200 aircraft were delivered as Model 1300s.
Later Model B200 aircraft were fitted with Pro Line 21 avionics.
Model B200C is a version of B200 with cargo door.
Model B200C is available to order.
112 Model B200C aircraft were built as of the end of 2009.
47 of the 112 Model B200C aircraft were built for the United States Air Force as C-12Fs.
Later Model B200C aircraft were fitted with Pro Line 21 avionics.

text:
Model 200C
Civil equivalent to A200C, 36 built.
Model A200CT
Third military model, built for U.S. Army with cargo door and wingtip fuel tanks of Model 200T, 93 built.
Model 200CT
Civil equivalent to A200CT; one aircraft converted from Model 200C.

Model B200
Current baseline production model; updated version of Model 200. 1,157 built as of the end of 2009 including those converted to Model B200Ts. 12 aircraft delivered as Model 1300s. Later models fitted with Pro Line 21 avionics
Model B200C
Version of B200 with cargo door, available to order; 112 built as of the end of 2009, of which 47 were built for the United States Air Force as C-12Fs. Later models fitted with Pro Line 21 avionics.
